<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-08-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                    <head>No. 576.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Cushing</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-08-27"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 27,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 61.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I acknowledge the receipt of your interesting
                        dispatch of the 30th ultimo, No. 66, in relation to the possibility of
                        European intervention in the affairs of Spain. It confirms accounts which
                        have reached this country of atrocities in warfare which seem incredible in
                        the nineteenth century, which are without excuse or palliation, and a
                        continuance of which would be degrading to human nature.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                    <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>